The paper deals with the problem of guessing a random variable under a non-extensive entropic framework, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of the logarithmic norm entropy measure, which is a measure of statistical divergence and is commonly used in machine learning and data science (cs.MM, cs.SI). The paper also derives moment bounds for the guessing problem, which is a topic related to probability theory and statistics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of the guessing function, which is a topic related to optimization and machine learning (cs.LG).
